{
  "text": "Overall, the girls embodied, performed and (re)produced privileged subject positions, being 'nice', 'polite', 'kind' 'civilised' and able to regulate their emotions [CITATION_1] . Their femininities tended to be regulated into good behaviour (or carefully choreographed and limited 'naughty' behaviour) and avoided the shame of stepping outside of these well-regulated femininities [CITATION_2] . The girls claimed to get along with most of their peers, and behave kindly and politely, even to those whom they liked less, demonstrating empathy towards others to avoid leaving anyone out:",
  "correct_citation": {
